				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Polyvinyl chloride (PVC) is a significant plastic derived from petroleum. It has been widely used due to its superior properties. However, the volume of PVC is increasing in the natural world without proper management. A major issue in PVC recycling is the high chlorine content and hazardous additives in raw PVC. The granules resulting from the recycling process, known as recyclate, can be melted and remolded into different products. These granules can be used as feedstock for various products, such as plastic furniture, toys, and clothing.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">聚氯乙烯（PVC）是一种从石油中提炼出来的重要塑料。由于其优越的性能，它已被广泛使用。然而，自然界中的聚氯乙烯数量在不断增加，却没有得到适当的管理。聚氯乙烯回收利用的一个主要问题是聚氯乙烯原料中的高氯含量和有害添加剂。回收过程中产生的颗粒（称为回收料）可以熔化并重新塑造成不同的产品。这些颗粒可用作塑料家具、玩具和服装等各种产品的原料。</common:generalComment>
